      <preamble>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Regulations in exercise of the powers conferred by paragraphs 1(1) and (3) of schedule 2, and paragraph 21(b) of schedule 7, of the European Union (Withdrawal) Act 2018<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <part eId="part-1">
            <num>PART 1</num>
            <heading>Preliminary</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-1">
               <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
               <num>1.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>These Regulations may be cited as the Licensing (Amendment) (EU Exit) (Scotland) Regulations 2019 and come into force on exit day.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
         <part eId="part-2">
            <num>PART 2</num>
            <heading>Amendment of primary legislation</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-2">
               <heading>Amendment of the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982</heading>
               <num>2.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-2-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>Schedule 2 (control of sex shops) of the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982<noteRef href="#f00002" class="footnote" marker="2"/> is amended as follows.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-2-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In paragraph 9(3), in both sub-paragraphs (e) and (f), for “a member state of the European Union” substitute “the United Kingdom”.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-3">
               <heading>Amendment of the Crossbows Act 1987</heading>
               <num>3.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-3-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>The Crossbows Act 1987<noteRef href="#f00003" class="footnote" marker="3"/> is amended as follows.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-3-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In section 1A (defences), in subsection (3), after paragraph (a) insert—<mod>
                           <quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:TargetClass="unknown" ukl:TargetSubClass="unknown" ukl:Context="unknown">
                              <paragraph>
                                 <num>(aa)</num>
                                 <content>
                                    <p>a <abbr class="acronym" title="United Kingdom">UK</abbr> driving licence,</p>
                                 </content>
                              </paragraph>
                           </quotedStructure>
                        </mod>
                        <inline name="AppendText">.</inline>
                     </p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-4">
               <heading>Amendment of the Criminal Justice Act 1988</heading>
               <num>4.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-4-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>The Criminal Justice Act 1988<noteRef href="#f00004" class="footnote" marker="4"/> is amended as follows.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-4-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In section 141A (sale of knives and certain articles with blade or point to persons under eighteen), in subsection (4B), after paragraph (a) insert—<mod>
                           <quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:TargetClass="unknown" ukl:TargetSubClass="unknown" ukl:Context="unknown">
                              <paragraph>
                                 <num>(aa)</num>
                                 <content>
                                    <p>a UK driving licence,</p>
                                 </content>
                              </paragraph>
                           </quotedStructure>
                        </mod>
                        <inline name="AppendText">.</inline>
                     </p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-5">
               <heading>Amendment of the Licensing (Scotland) Act 2005</heading>
               <num>5.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-5-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>The Licensing (Scotland) Act 2005<noteRef href="#f00005" class="footnote" marker="5"/> is amended as follows.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-5-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In section 102 (sale of alcohol to a child or young person), in subsection (4), after paragraph (a) insert—<mod>
                           <quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:TargetClass="unknown" ukl:TargetSubClass="unknown" ukl:Context="unknown">
                              <paragraph>
                                 <num>(aa)</num>
                                 <content>
                                    <p>a UK driving licence,</p>
                                 </content>
                              </paragraph>
                           </quotedStructure>
                        </mod>
                        <inline name="AppendText">.</inline>
                     </p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-5-3">
                  <num>(3)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In section 108 (delivery of alcohol by or to a child or young person), in subsection (7), after paragraph (a) insert—<mod>
                           <quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:TargetClass="unknown" ukl:TargetSubClass="unknown" ukl:Context="unknown">
                              <paragraph>
                                 <num>(aa)</num>
                                 <content>
                                    <p>a UK driving licence,</p>
                                 </content>
                              </paragraph>
                           </quotedStructure>
                        </mod>
                        <inline name="AppendText">.</inline>
                     </p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
         <part eId="part-3">
            <num>PART 3</num>
            <heading>Amendment of subordinate legislation</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-6">
               <heading>Amendment of the Sale of Alcohol to Children and Young Persons (Scotland) Regulations 2007</heading>
               <num>6.</num>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-6-1">
                  <num>(1)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>The Sale of Alcohol to Children and Young Persons (Scotland) Regulations 2007<noteRef href="#f00006" class="footnote" marker="6"/> are amended as follows.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
               <paragraph eId="regulation-6-2">
                  <num>(2)</num>
                  <content>
                     <p>In regulation 2(2)(c), omit “(other than the United Kingdom)”.</p>
                  </content>
               </paragraph>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
         <part eId="part-4">
            <num>PART 4</num>
            <heading>Saving provision</heading>
            <hcontainer name="regulation" eId="regulation-7">
               <heading>Saving provision</heading>
               <num>7.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>The amendments made by regulation 2 do not apply in respect of an application for the grant or renewal of a licence under paragraph 6 of schedule 2 of the Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982 received by the local authority before exit day.</p>
               </content>
            </hcontainer>
         </part>
